In <3mrgq1$k5c@news.primenet.com>, zachg@primenet.com (Zak) writes:
>Could someone suggest a method for copying a WPS folder and
>all the objects beneath it?  I tried zipping the appropriate subdirectory
>of C:\desktop complete w/ EAs but that only got the sub-Folders not 
>the program objects contained in the folders.  Where are those little
>buggers physically stored?

Program objects are stored in the os2.ini file.  They know what
executable they point to using information stored in os2sys.ini.
You cannot just copy the folder onto another machine if it has
abstract objects in it (program objects are abstract).
I don't know if Warp provides this capability but it used to
be that there was no way to copy an abstract object to diskette.
To test it, drag a program object to the A drive and see if it allows
you to. 

--Mindy



